 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","title":"[audit][test] Decouple Trace capture from implicit stderr printing in TestLogger","description":"TestLogger::new(TestLogLevel::Trace) currently flips verbose=true, so asking for maximal event capture also causes immediate stderr emission from library test-support code. Make verbosity explicit instead of coupling it to Trace, add regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925143002Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925119328Z","close_reason":"Completed: TestLogger trace capture no longer implies verbose stderr output; file-local rustfmt and UBS clean, rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed, focused rch test passed, clippy remains blocked only by unrelated src/channel/oneshot.rs lint frontier","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
