+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.2","title":"[audit][grpc] Keep shared service health registered until last HealthReporter drops","description":"Audit follow-up in src/grpc/health.rs. HealthReporter currently clears its service status unconditionally on Drop. If multiple HealthReporter instances exist for the same service, dropping any one of them removes the shared registration even while another reporter for that same service is still alive and may still be marking it serving/not-serving. Scope: retain per-service reporter ownership so only the final reporter drop clears status, add focused regression coverage for multi-reporter lifecycle semantics, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:23:31.116168820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:39:02.938626779Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:39:02.938585803Z","close_reason":"Fixed grpc/health multi-reporter lifecycle bug; added regression; targeted remote test and remote cargo check passed; fmt check passed; remote clippy blocked by rch instability","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:23:31.116168820Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
