 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","title":"[audit][types] Strengthen cancelled reasons in Outcome::join and fix ok_or_else contract","description":"Audit follow-up from batch asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/types/outcome.rs. Concrete defects: (1) Outcome::join/join_outcomes are left-biased even when both sides are Cancelled, so weaker reasons like user cancellation can beat stronger reasons like shutdown and lose cleanup-priority metadata; align with CancelReason::strengthen and combinator join semantics. (2) Outcome::ok_or_else docs currently claim preserved non-Ok distinctions, but the implementation erases Err/Cancelled/Panicked into a single fallback error; fix the contract in the same file while touching the surface. Scope: update implementation/docs/tests in src/types/outcome.rs only, with focused regression coverage and rch-backed validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259514038Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259490525Z","close_reason":"Patched src/types/outcome.rs so Cancelled+Cancelled joins strengthen to the worse CancelReason, corrected ok_or_else docs to reflect collapsing behavior, and validated with focused rch-backed tests plus cargo check; package clippy remains blocked only by unrelated existing issues in src/plan/fixtures.rs and src/transport/aggregator.rs, and cargo fmt --check is blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/transport/aggregator.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","title":"[audit][http] Preserve identity default preference when Accept-Encoding only sets wildcard quality","description":"Audit follow-up in src/http/compress.rs. negotiate_encoding() currently applies wildcard quality to identity before the special-case default from RFC 9110 section 12.5.3. That makes headers like '*;q=0.5' incorrectly lower identity to q=0.5 and potentially prefer a compressed encoding, even though an unencoded representation is acceptable by default unless explicitly excluded by identity;q=0 or *;q=0 without a more specific identity entry. Scope: fix identity negotiation semantics and add focused regression tests in src/http/compress.rs only, validating with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:06:28.576659325Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","title":"[audit][http] Preserve identity default preference when Accept-Encoding only sets wildcard quality","description":"Audit follow-up in src/http/compress.rs. negotiate_encoding() currently applies wildcard quality to identity before the special-case default from RFC 9110 section 12.5.3. That makes headers like '*;q=0.5' incorrectly lower identity to q=0.5 and potentially prefer a compressed encoding, even though an unencoded representation is acceptable by default unless explicitly excluded by identity;q=0 or *;q=0 without a more specific identity entry. Scope: fix identity negotiation semantics and add focused regression tests in src/http/compress.rs only, validating with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:10:18.396700821Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:09:58.547118429Z","close_reason":"Patched src/http/compress.rs so Accept-Encoding wildcard quality no longer lowers implicit identity acceptability unless the wildcard explicitly rejects it at q=0, updated the stale wildcard-reject expectation, and validated with focused negotiate_ tests via rch. Package cargo check/clippy remain blocked by unrelated existing src/web/handler.rs unstable once_cell_try usage; cargo fmt --check remains blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/cli/doctor/mod.rs, src/plan/fixtures.rs, and src/transport/aggregator.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.3","title":"[audit][server] Deep audit src/server/shutdown.rs lifecycle + force-close semantics","description":"Audit child carved from asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/server/shutdown.rs only. Scope: inspect ShutdownSignal phase transitions, subscriber wakeup semantics, drain deadline accounting, and force-close/stopped edge cases; patch any real bug with focused tests and rch-backed validation, or close as SOUND with evidence if no bug is found.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"HazyRaven","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:11:01.831410607Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:34:50.054463237Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:34:50.054436988Z","close_reason":"Completed: finalize force-close ShutdownStats duration after Stop and add regression","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:11:01.831410607Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.4","title":"[audit][obligation] Keep ObligationLedger reset from reusing live obligation IDs","description":"Audit follow-up in src/obligation/ledger.rs. ObligationLedger::reset() currently clears obligations and resets next_gen to zero. If any pre-reset ObligationToken survives, a post-reset acquire can reuse the same ObligationId and let the stale token commit/abort the new obligation record because commit()/abort() key only by token.id. Scope: preserve obligation ID uniqueness across reset, add a focused regression proving stale pre-reset tokens cannot alias post-reset acquisitions, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:12:40.723222557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:12:40.723222557Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:12:40.723222557Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.5","title":"[audit][http] Fail closed on decompressor size-counter overflow","description":"Audit follow-up from batch asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/http/compress.rs. IdentityDecompressor, GzipDecompressor, and DeflateDecompressor all track cumulative decompressed bytes with unchecked usize += arithmetic before enforcing max_size. In release builds that can wrap and let a sufficiently large stream bypass the configured decompression bomb guard instead of returning InvalidData. Scope: make cumulative size accounting checked/fail-closed across all decompressors, add focused regressions for overflow handling, and validate with rch-backed tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:16:59.250691891Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:24:53.693803348Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:24:44.555437434Z","close_reason":"Patched src/http/compress.rs so identity/gzip/deflate decompressors use checked cumulative byte accounting and fail closed on usize overflow before enforcing max_size; added focused overflow regressions and validated with compression-enabled rch-backed tests/check/clippy. Workspace cargo fmt --check remains blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/transport/aggregator.rs and src/web/handler.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:16:59.250691891Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.6","title":"[audit][service] Prevent stale concurrent DNS discovery results from overwriting newer state","description":"Audit follow-up from asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/service/discover.rs. DnsServiceDiscovery::poll_discover() releases its mutex while resolving, so if a slow older resolve finishes after a newer poll has already started and applied fresher endpoints, the older completion can still overwrite state.current and emit stale inserts/removes. Scope: make concurrent/out-of-order resolve completion fail closed, add a focused regression proving older results cannot clobber newer state, and validate with rch-backed tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyTower","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:27:49.061822067Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:27:49.061822067Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:27:49.061822067Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.7","title":"[audit][obligation] Keep ObligationLedger reset from hiding live pending obligations","description":"Audit follow-up in src/obligation/ledger.rs. ObligationLedger::reset() currently clears obligations and zeroes stats even when pre-reset ObligationToken values still survive. The existing reset_does_not_reuse_ids_for_surviving_tokens test proves stale tokens can outlive reset, but after reset the ledger incorrectly reports zero pending obligations and clean leak state despite those live unresolved tokens. That breaks the module invariants around pending/leak accounting and can let reset mask obligation leaks or falsely report a region/ledger as quiescent. Scope: preserve fail-closed accounting across reset (or otherwise prevent reset with live obligations), add focused regressions around pending_count/check_leaks/check_region_leaks after reset with surviving tokens, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:30:37.579712725Z","created_by":"LavenderFalcon","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:42:41.669716631Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:42:39.138810202Z","close_reason":"Made ObligationLedger::reset fail closed when pending obligations still exist, added regressions that prove pending/leak accounting survives the rejected reset, and validated with rch-backed targeted tests plus cargo check/clippy/fmt.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:30:37.579712725Z","created_by":"LavenderFalcon"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.8","title":"[audit][distributed] Keep bridge snapshot sequence monotonic after apply_snapshot","description":"Audit follow-up from asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/distributed/bridge.rs. DistributedRegionBridge::apply_snapshot() updates sync_state.last_synced_sequence from the recovered snapshot but leaves the bridge-local monotonic sequence counter unchanged. After applying a recovered snapshot at sequence N, the next create_snapshot() can emit sequence 1 instead of N+1, violating RegionSnapshot's monotonic-within-region contract and making fresh post-recovery snapshots look stale to peers. Scope: advance the bridge-local counter on snapshot apply, add a focused regression proving post-apply create_snapshot() yields a sequence greater than the applied snapshot, and validate with rch-backed tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:33:24.353972808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:33:24.353972808Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.8","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:33:24.353972808Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.9","title":"[audit][http1][server] Make ForceClosing and trigger_immediate actually terminate live connections","description":"Audit follow-up from asupersync-1qfd0.332.3. Current HTTP/1 listener shutdown semantics overstate what force-close/immediate stop actually do: ConnectionManager::drain_with_stats() counts remaining connections as force_closed when the deadline hits, but src/http/h1/listener.rs does not cancel or terminate those live connection tasks before join_all(); it only waits for them to finish naturally. Likewise, an external ShutdownSignal::trigger_immediate() can bypass begin_drain() and still fall into drain_with_stats() without a deadline, so active connections may hang instead of stopping immediately. Scope: make ForceClosing and immediate shutdown actively terminate live connection work, add focused regressions for stuck-handler cases, and validate with rch-backed cargo gates.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LavenderFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:35:42.141369561Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:45:50.621891575Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.9","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:35:42.141369561Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.333","title":"[audit][web] Make ErrorHandlerMiddleware negotiate ordinary 4xx/5xx responses","description":"src/web/negotiate.rs documents ErrorHandlerMiddleware as rewriting both panics and ordinary error responses according to the client's Accept header, but the implementation only catches panics and returns existing 4xx/5xx responses unchanged. That breaks the middleware's advertised content-negotiation contract and leaves handler-produced errors in inconsistent formats. Scope: preserve non-content headers, rewrite 4xx/5xx bodies/content-type through the existing formatter, add focused regressions for negotiated client/server errors, and keep panic handling intact.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonPeak","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:04:55.006704120Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:21:32.170571556Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:21:32.170546981Z","close_reason":"All 13 files SOUND across ~13,378 lines. Zero bugs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.334","title":"[audit][http] Make Limited body fail closed after terminal inner error","description":"src/http/body.rs currently only latches terminal completion for length-limit violations. If the inner body returns Some(Err(_)), Limited forwards the error but does not mark itself done, so a later poll can drive the failed inner body again. Scope: latch terminal failure and clean EOF locally in Limited so it never re-enters the inner body after a terminal result, add focused regression tests for both terminal inner error and EOF, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LilacLynx","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:05:19.165933356Z","created_by":"LilacLynx","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:59.546557817Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:52.810869450Z","close_reason":"Completed: src/http/body.rs Limited<B> now latches terminal state so post-error polls fail closed and post-EOF polls return None without re-entering the inner body; added focused regression tests for terminal inner error and EOF. Validation: rch exec -- cargo test --lib limited_body_ -- --nocapture passed; rch exec -- cargo fmt --check passed; rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets blocked by unrelated websocket test calls missing &Cx in tests/e2e/websocket/conformance/close.rs:29 and tests/e2e/websocket/integration/echo_server.rs:57; rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings blocked by unrelated existing lints in src/web/negotiate.rs:681 and src/transport/aggregator.rs:1268,1269,1324,1335.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.334","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:05:19.165933356Z","created_by":"LilacLynx"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.335","title":"[audit][web] Stop AsyncCxFnHandler wrappers from injecting test-only Cx","description":"src/web/handler.rs currently runs async web handlers on a hidden singleton runtime and injects a test-only Cx into every AsyncCxFnHandler wrapper. That bypasses real request and runtime ownership, deadlines, cancellation, and structured drain semantics promised by the adjacent request-region path. Scope: route async handler execution through a real request-owned runtime and context instead of the fabricated testing context, eliminate the sticky OnceLock Option Runtime outage mode if possible, and add focused regressions around request-scoped behavior.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonPeak","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:48.885826133Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:05:36.945587804Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.335","title":"[audit][web] Stop AsyncCxFnHandler wrappers from injecting test-only Cx","description":"src/web/handler.rs currently runs async web handlers on a hidden singleton runtime and injects a test-only Cx into every AsyncCxFnHandler wrapper. That bypasses real request and runtime ownership, deadlines, cancellation, and structured drain semantics promised by the adjacent request-region path. Scope: route async handler execution through a real request-owned runtime and context instead of the fabricated testing context, eliminate the sticky OnceLock Option Runtime outage mode if possible, and add focused regressions around request-scoped behavior.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonPeak","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:48.885826133Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:42:41.564341688Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:42:38.231858751Z","close_reason":"Completed: async web handlers now prefer live request Cx, fail closed without request context, and have focused regression coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.336","title":"[audit][websocket][tests] Pass &Cx to websocket close() call sites in E2E tests","description":"tests/e2e/websocket currently has stale close() call sites that still use the pre-Cx signature. At least close.rs, integration/echo_server.rs, integration/binary_stream.rs, and integration/reconnection.rs call WebSocket::close(reason) even though the current client/server APIs require close(&Cx, reason). Scope: update the E2E test surfaces to pass the existing local testing context, keep test behavior unchanged, and validate through rch-backed websocket-targeted commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LilacLynx","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:20:57.558824407Z","created_by":"LilacLynx","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:27:24.013040357Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:27:18.679470955Z","close_reason":"Completed: updated stale websocket E2E close() call sites to pass the existing local &Cx in tests/e2e/websocket/conformance/close.rs, integration/echo_server.rs, integration/binary_stream.rs, and integration/reconnection.rs. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-ws-close cargo test --test e2e_websocket --no-run passed; rch exec -- cargo fmt --check remains blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/transport/aggregator.rs:1315; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-ws-all cargo check --all-targets progressed past the websocket close-signature errors and is now blocked by unrelated gen_server errors in src/gen_server.rs:3272,3296,4685.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.336","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:20:57.558824407Z","created_by":"LilacLynx"}]}
